---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

export const meta = {
  title: "SPYI Dividend Analysis & History",
  description: "Uncover the latest SPYI dividend yield, historic payouts, and tax-efficient strategies. Is this high-income ETF the right addition to your portfolio for 2026?",
  category: "tool",
  published: "2026-03-15",
};

const schema = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "SPYI Dividend Analysis & History",
    "description": meta.description,
    "datePublished": meta.published,
    "author": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "Westmount Fundamentals"
    }
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the spyi dividend history?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "SPYI has consistently distributed income since its launch. Annual payouts per share were $1.89 in 2022, $5.31 in 2023, $6.12 in 2024, and $6.15 in 2025."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the spyi dividend?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "The SPYI dividend is a monthly distribution generated by holding S&P 500 stocks while actively utilizing a tax-efficient call options strategy."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the spyi dividend yield?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Currently, SPYI offers an estimated dividend yield of 11.84%, derived from both standard equity dividends and options premiums."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the projected spyi dividend yield 2025?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "While forward yields fluctuate with market volatility, the projected SPYI dividend yield remained steadily around the 11% to 12% mark throughout 2025."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How does SPYI manage tax efficiency on its dividends?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "SPYI utilizes Section 1256 contracts for its options strategy, meaning 60% of the gains are taxed as long-term capital gains, offering significant tax advantages compared to standard ordinary income dividends."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
];
---
<SiteLayout site="westmount" title={meta.title} description={meta.description} canonical="https://westmountfundamentals.com/spyi-dividend-history" schema={schema}>
  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="hero">
      <h1>SPYI Dividend Analysis & History</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Tax-efficient high-income generation via the S&P 500</p>
    </div>

    <section>
      <h2>SPYI Overview & Key Metrics</h2>
      <p>The <strong>NEOS S&P 500 High Income ETF (SPYI)</strong> provides a unique approach to generating yield from the broader market. SPYI holds the individual stocks of the S&P 500 and overlays an actively managed call option strategy to generate supplemental income. This makes it a popular choice for investors looking to balance capital appreciation with a robust monthly <strong>spyi dividend</strong>.</p>

      <p>A key differentiator for SPYI is its focus on tax efficiency. By trading SPX Index options classified as Section 1256 contracts, a significant portion of its distributed gains receives favorable long-term capital gains tax treatment regardless of the holding period.</p>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>Current Snapshot</h3>
        <table>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <th>Current Dividend Yield</th>
              <td>11.84%</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th>Price-to-Earnings (P/E) Ratio</th>
              <td>26.73</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th>Assets Under Management (AUM)</th>
              <td>$8.06 Billion</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th>Category</th>
              <td>Derivative Income</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th>Payout Frequency</th>
              <td>Monthly</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <p>At an 11.84% yield, SPYI offers an attractive income profile while attempting to capture more of the S&P 500's upside compared to traditional at-the-money covered call funds. This is achieved by utilizing an out-of-the-money options strategy.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>SPYI Dividend History</h2>
      <p>Analyzing the <strong>spyi dividend history</strong> shows a reliable track record of monthly distributions. Because the fund's income is partly dependent on options premiums, payouts can vary based on market volatility (VIX). However, the fund managers strive for a consistent monthly distribution profile.</p>

      <p>Below is the historical annual payout data per share:</p>

      <div class="card">
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Year</th>
              <th>Total Annual Payout (per share)</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>2022</td>
              <td>$1.89 (Partial Year)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>2023</td>
              <td>$5.31</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>2024</td>
              <td>$6.12</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>2025</td>
              <td>$6.15</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>2026 (YTD)</td>
              <td>$1.05</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <p>The growth from 2023 to 2024 reflects the fund capitalizing on both favorable market conditions and elevated volatility premiums. Recent monthly distributions in late 2025 and early 2026 have consistently hovered around $0.52 to $0.53 per share, confirming stability in its <strong>spyi dividend yield</strong>.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Dividend Reinvestment (DRIP) Calculator</h2>
      <p>Compounding a double-digit yield through a Dividend Reinvestment Plan (DRIP) can significantly accelerate portfolio growth. Use the calculator below to estimate your annual income assuming you reinvest all monthly distributions back into SPYI shares. Keep in mind that the exact <strong>spyi dividend yield 2025</strong> and beyond depends heavily on prevailing market volatility.</p>

      <div class="card calculator-container">
        <h3>Project Your SPYI Income</h3>
        <div style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">
          <label for="sharesInput" style="display:block; margin-bottom:0.5rem; font-weight:bold;">Shares Owned:</label>
          <input type="number" id="sharesInput" value="100" min="1" style="width:100%; padding:0.75rem; border-radius:6px; border:1px solid var(--border-color); background:var(--bg-color); color:var(--text-primary);">
        </div>
        <div style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">
          <label for="priceInput" style="display:block; margin-bottom:0.5rem; font-weight:bold;">Current Price per Share ($):</label>
          <input type="number" id="priceInput" value="50.00" step="0.01" style="width:100%; padding:0.75rem; border-radius:6px; border:1px solid var(--border-color); background:var(--bg-color); color:var(--text-primary);">
        </div>
        <button id="calcBtn" style="background:var(--accent-color); color:#fff; border:none; padding:0.75rem 1.5rem; border-radius:6px; font-weight:bold; cursor:pointer; width:100%;">Calculate Annual Income</button>

        <div id="calcResults" style="margin-top: 1.5rem; display:none; padding:1rem; background:var(--bg-color); border-radius:6px; border:1px solid var(--border-color);">
          <p style="margin:0 0 0.5rem 0;">Estimated Annual Income (No Reinvestment): <strong id="resNoDrip" style="color:var(--accent-color); font-size:1.2rem;">$0.00</strong></p>
          <p style="margin:0;">Estimated Annual Income (With DRIP): <strong id="resDrip" style="color:var(--accent-color); font-size:1.2rem;">$0.00</strong></p>
          <p style="font-size:0.8rem; color:var(--text-secondary); margin-top:0.5rem;">*Assumes a static 11.84% yield and constant share price.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Comparison to Category Average</h2>
      <p>When placed alongside other broad-market derivative income ETFs, SPYI distinguishes itself through its specific tax-advantaged strategy. While funds like <a href="/spy-dividend">SPY</a> offer standard equity yields near 1.06%, SPYI pushes that yield closer to 12% by selling upside call options. Compared to ultra-high-yield funds like <a href="/ymax-dividend-history">YMAX</a>, SPYI offers a much more balanced approach, prioritizing the preservation of principal while still generating substantial double-digit income.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="faq-section">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <details>
        <summary>What is the spyi dividend history?</summary>
        <p>SPYI has consistently distributed income since its launch. Annual payouts per share were $1.89 in 2022, $5.31 in 2023, $6.12 in 2024, and $6.15 in 2025.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What is the spyi dividend?</summary>
        <p>The SPYI dividend is a monthly distribution generated by holding S&P 500 stocks while actively utilizing a tax-efficient call options strategy.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What is the spyi dividend yield?</summary>
        <p>Currently, SPYI offers an estimated dividend yield of 11.84%, derived from both standard equity dividends and options premiums.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What is the projected spyi dividend yield 2025?</summary>
        <p>While forward yields fluctuate with market volatility, the projected SPYI dividend yield remained steadily around the 11% to 12% mark throughout 2025.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How does SPYI manage tax efficiency on its dividends?</summary>
        <p>SPYI utilizes Section 1256 contracts for its options strategy, meaning 60% of the gains are taxed as long-term capital gains, offering significant tax advantages compared to standard ordinary income dividends.</p>
      </details>
    </section>
  </div>

  <script is:inline>
    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
      const calcBtn = document.getElementById('calcBtn');
      if(calcBtn) {
        calcBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
          const shares = parseFloat(document.getElementById('sharesInput').value) || 0;
          const price = parseFloat(document.getElementById('priceInput').value) || 0;
          const yieldPct = 0.1184; // 11.84%

          const principal = shares * price;
          const incomeNoDrip = principal * yieldPct;

          // Simple monthly compounding approximation for DRIP
          const monthlyRate = yieldPct / 12;
          const finalValue = principal * Math.pow(1 + monthlyRate, 12);
          const incomeDrip = finalValue - principal;

          document.getElementById('resNoDrip').textContent = '$' + incomeNoDrip.toLocaleString(undefined, {minimumFractionDigits: 2, maximumFractionDigits: 2});
          document.getElementById('resDrip').textContent = '$' + incomeDrip.toLocaleString(undefined, {minimumFractionDigits: 2, maximumFractionDigits: 2});
          document.getElementById('calcResults').style.display = 'block';
        });
      }
    });
  </script>

  <style is:inline>
    /* NO :root block. Use CSS vars: --bg-color, --card-bg, --border-color, --accent-color, --text-primary, --text-secondary */
    .page-content { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1.5rem; }
    .hero { text-align: center; padding: 3rem 0 2rem; }
    .hero h1 { font-size: 2.2rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    .subtitle { color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 1.1rem; }
    .card { background: var(--card-bg); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; margin: 1.5rem 0; }
    table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1.5rem 0; }
    th, td { padding: 0.75rem 1rem; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color); }
    th { font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 0.85rem; text-transform: uppercase; }
    .faq-section details { margin: 1rem 0; padding: 1rem; background: var(--card-bg); border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid var(--border-color); }
    .faq-section summary { font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; }
    .calculator-container label { color: var(--text-primary); }
    a { color: var(--accent-color); text-decoration: none; }
    a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
  </style>
</SiteLayout>
